    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-11-17T18:05:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-11-17T18:05:00-05:00" n="329"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                <head>329. Telegram From the Department of State to the Embassy in the Congo<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d329fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1964–66, POL 23–9 THE
                        CONGO. Top Secret; Flash; Exdis. Drafted by McElhiney and Hoffacker; cleared
                        by Deputy Assistant Secretary for <gloss target="#t_EUR_1">EUR</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CRC_1">Robert C. Creel</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_SJJ_1">Sisco</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_WGM_1"
                            >Williams</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_PJI_1"
                        >Palmer</persName>; and approved by <persName corresp="#p_HWA_1"
                            >Harriman</persName>. Repeated to Brussels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-11-17T18:05:00-05:00">November 17, 1964, 6:05 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1275. Subject: Dragon Rouge. Brussels 966 and 967.<note n="2" xml:id="d329fn2"
                        >See <ref target="#d328fn2">Document 328 and footnote 2</ref>
                        thereto.</note> We agree approach in general terms to <persName
                        corresp="#p_TMK_1">Tshombe</persName> is matter some urgency. We giving
                    urgent consideration to form of request from <persName corresp="#p_KEJ_1"
                        >Kasavubu</persName> or <persName corresp="#p_TMK_1">Tshombe</persName>
                    designed inter alia assure best possible position in <gloss target="#t_UN_1"
                        >UN</gloss> and will send our views soonest to Brussels for coordination
                    with <gloss target="#t_GOB_1">GOB</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Meanwhile you should not give consent to de <persName corresp="#p_KCD_1"
                        >Kerchove</persName> for approach by him to <persName corresp="#p_TMK_1"
                        >Tshombe</persName>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">For Brussels:</hi> You may inform <persName corresp="#p_SPH_1"
                        >Spaak</persName> and/or <persName corresp="#p_DVE_1">Davignon</persName>
                    foregoing, adding we hope send our views later tonight.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RDE_1">Rusk</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
